<div id="pf72" class="pf w0 ha" data-page-no="72"><div class="pc pc72 w0 ha"><img class="bi x0 y0 w1 hb" alt="" src="bg72.png"/><div class="t m20c x87 h22 ya90 ff5 fs13 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Bible Study Guide for Third Quarter, 2002 </div><div class="t m35f x5f h1e ya91 ff4 fs12 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Kings and Chronicles: Rebellion and Reformation, </div><div class="t m7d3 xb9 h1e ya92 ff2 fs12 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">by James </div><div class="t m51e x70 h1e ya93 ff2 fs12 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Zackrison, begins with a study of the days of the monarchies under </div><div class="t m667 x70 h1e ya94 ff2 fs12 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">David and Solomon. It follows the split of these two kingdoms and the </div><div class="t mff x70 h1e ya95 ff2 fs12 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">separate path each took, ending with the Babylonian captivity of the </div><div class="t m27a x70 h1e y861 ff2 fs12 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">southern kingdom. </div><div class="t m6a2 x70 h22 ya96 ff5 fs13 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Lesson 1: A Rough Start (June 29â€”July 5) </div><div class="t m21b x6c h28 ya97 ff5 fs12 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">THE WEEK AT A GLANCE: </div><div class="t m2f2 x6c h1e ya98 ff4 fs12 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Sunday: &quot;I </div><div class="t m2b0 x45 h1e ya99 ff2 fs12 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Will Be King.&quot; </div><div class="t m481 x70 h1e ya9a ff4 fs12 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Monday: </div><div class="t m3c x7 h1e ya9a ff2 fs12 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Forgiven Sin. </div><div class="t m334 x70 h1e ya9b ff4 fs12 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Tuesday: </div><div class="t m367 x1 h1e y9d7 ff2 fs12 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The Wages of Forgiven Sin. </div><div class="t m7d4 x70 h1e ya9c ff4 fs12 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Wednesday: </div><div class="t m132 x48 h1e ya9d ff2 fs12 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The Plot Uncovered (Read 1 Kings 1:11-27). </div><div class="t m305 x70 h1e y5ae ff4 fs12 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Thursday: </div><div class="t m33b x42 h1e ya9e ff2 fs12 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The Plot Foiled (1 Kings 1:28-53). </div><div class="t m240 x70 h28 ya2c ff5 fs12 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">MEMORY TEXT: </div><div class="t m250 x41 h1e ya2c ff2 fs12 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Genesis 18:18. </div><div class="t m240 x6c h28 ya9f ff5 fs12 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">SABBATH GEM: </div><div class="t m4a3 xca h1e ya9f ff2 fs12 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Kings and Chronicles are, in many ways, a family </div><div class="t m7d5 x5d h1e yaa0 ff2 fs12 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">history of those descended from faithful (but flawed) Abraham. </div><div class="t m502 x5d h1e ya68 ff2 fs12 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Interspersed amidst the failures recorded in Kings and Chronicles </div><div class="t m226 x5d h1e yaa1 ff2 fs12 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">are glimpses of divine light. </div><div class="t m7bf x70 h22 y9e0 ff5 fs13 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Lesson 2: The Wisdom of Solomon (July 6-12) </div><div class="t m236 x6c h28 y5b3 ff5 fs12 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">THE WEEK AT A GLANCE: </div><div class="t m60a x6c h1e yaa2 ff4 fs12 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Sunday: </div><div class="t m74c x7d h1e yaa2 ff2 fs12 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Deathbed Admonition. </div><div class="t m334 x70 h1e yaa3 ff4 fs12 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Monday: </div><div class="t m24f x7 h1e y8f5 ff2 fs12 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Adonijah Revisited. </div><div class="t m6c6 x70 h1e y8f3 ff4 fs12 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Tuesday: </div><div class="t mb3 x7 h1e y8f3 ff2 fs12 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Abiathar, Joab, and Shimei (Read 1 Kings 2:26-45). </div><div class="t m39 x70 h1e yaa4 ff4 fs12 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Wednesday: </div><div class="t m2ee x48 h1e y8f6 ff2 fs12 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Solomon&apos;s Dream (1 Kings 3:1-10). </div><div class="t m57d x70 h1e y8f7 ff4 fs12 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Thursday: </div><div class="t m302 xa9 h1e y8f7 ff2 fs12 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">An Understanding Heart (1 Kings 3:10-16). </div><div class="t m7d4 x6c h28 y8f9 ff5 fs12 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">MEMORY TEXT:1 </div><div class="t m323 x1d h1e y8f9 ff2 fs12 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Kings 3:14. </div><div class="t m6f7 x6c h28 y86b ff5 fs12 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">SABBATH GEM: </div><div class="t m230 x1c h1e y8fa ff2 fs12 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">How thankful we should be that God is still will-</div><div class="t m307 x5d h1e yaa5 ff2 fs12 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">ing to work with us, no matter how much we have messed up along </div><div class="t m3d0 x5d h1e y8fc ff2 fs12 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the way. </div><div class="t m585 x6c h28 ya6e ff5 fs12 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Lessons for the Visually Impaired </div><div class="t m2bf x5d h1e y8ff ff2 fs12 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The regular Adult Sabbath School Bible Study Guide is available </div><div class="t m519 x6c h1e ya70 ff2 fs12 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">free each month in braille and on audiocassette for visually impaired </div><div class="t m5a2 x6c h1e y871 ff2 fs12 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">and physically handicapped persons who cannot read normal ink print. </div><div class="t m251 x6c h1e y901 ff2 fs12 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">This includes individuals who because of arthritis, multiple sclerosis, </div><div class="t m175 x6c h1e yaa6 ff2 fs12 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">paralysis, accident, old age, and so forth, cannot hold or focus on </div><div class="t m226 x6c h1e ya71 ff2 fs12 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">normal ink-print publications. Contact the Christian Record Services, </div><div class="t m509 x6c h1e yaa7 ff2 fs12 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Box 6097, Lincoln, NE 68506-0097. </div><div class="t mb x6c h1e yaa8 ff2 fs12 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">112 </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
